&lt;p&gt;US President Donald Trump on Tuesday distanced himself from recent reports claiming he encouraged Ukraine to launch strikes deep into Russian territory, firmly stating that Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy &quot;should not target Moscow.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The statement came just a day after Trump revealed a more aggressive approach toward Russia, which includes a fresh round of military aid to Ukraine&amp;mdash;part of what he described as a &quot;toughened stance.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;I&amp;rsquo;m not on anyone&amp;rsquo;s side,&quot; Trump told reporters gathered on the South Lawn of the White House. &quot;I&amp;rsquo;m on the side of humanity, because I want to stop the killing.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
